        "created_at": "2023-04-30T16:13:41.281Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I see \u201cNicolas Bottling\u201d on old Bordeaux sometimes and I am curious what that means?   I thought maybe it meant the wine was bottled offsite but the bottles also always still say Mis en Bouteille au Chateau.  Can anyone explain what it means? And are \u201cNicolas Bottlings\u201d less desirable than non-nicolas bottlings?</p>\n<p>Thanks very much in advance.</p>",
