        "created_at": "2023-04-30T16:34:46.036Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Nicolas kept big stocks and stored them in their Paris cellars in optimal conditions, releasing them at maturity. The labels were stamped with the red Nicolas roundel, which was taken as a good sign. Some wine counterfeiters have favored Nicolas-stamped labels, however.</p>",
